Introduction to GGPLOT

This is an R Markdown Notebook. When you execute code within the notebook, the results appear beneath the code.

Try executing this chunk by clicking the Run button within the chunk or by placing your cursor inside it and pressing Ctrl+Shift+Enter.

bodysize <- read_csv("children_bodysize.csv")%>%
mutate(height = stature/10,
        age = age/12,
        year_old = floor(age),
        gender = factor(gender) )
Rows: 3741 Columns: 12── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────
Delimiter: ","
chr  (1): gender
dbl (11): weight, stature, head, shoulder, hand_l, hand_w, c...
ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
bodysize
plot(height~age,data=bodysize)

ggplot()+ geom_point(data=bodysize,mapping=aes(x=age,y=height,color=gender))

ggplot()+ geom_point(data=bodysize,mapping=aes(x=age,y=height,color=gender,size=0.5,alpha=0.8))

ggplot() + geom_histogram(data=filter(bodysize,year_old==15),mapping=aes(x=height),binwidth=5)

ggplot() + geom_density(data=filter(bodysize,year_old==15),mapping=aes(x=height,color=gender))

ggplot() + geom_violin(data=filter(bodysize,year_old==15),mapping = aes(y = height, x=gender, color=gender, fill=gender))

ggplot(data = bodysize, 
       mapping = aes(x=age, y=height, color=gender)) +
  geom_point(size=0.1,alpha=0.8) +
  geom_smooth()

ggplot(data = bodysize, 
       mapping = aes(x=age, y=height)) +
  geom_point(size=0.1,alpha=0.8) +
  geom_smooth() + facet_wrap(~gender)

ggplot(data = bodysize, 
       mapping = aes(x=age, y=height)) +
  geom_point(size=0.1,alpha=0.8) +
  geom_smooth() + facet_wrap(~gender)

ggplot(data = bodysize, 
       mapping = aes(x=age, y=height)) +
  geom_point(size=0.1,alpha=0.8) +
  geom_smooth() + facet_wrap(~gender)

ggplot(data = bodysize) +
  geom_density( mapping = aes(x = height, color=gender) ) +
  facet_wrap(~year_old)

bodysize%>%
  filter(age>=13,age<=18)%>%
  ggplot()+
  geom_density(mapping=aes(x=height,color=gender))+
  facet_wrap(~year_old)

bodysize %>% 
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x=year_old, y=foot_l)) +
  geom_jitter(size=.1)
